  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You partake in a ritual of sacrifice to boost the power of your weapon for a brief time, forming seals of blood along your body. You bend down on one knee and strike yourself with your weapon on your back, losing hit points equal to twice your [Weapon's Damage].</p><p>As you strike yourself, your lacerations morph into blood-red fuinjutsu seals, bestowing you with Strength and granting you a prominent red aura of chakra. For the duration, jutsu you cast that require a Flail weapon as a component have their cost reduced by -3, gain a +1d4 bonus to attack rolls or +2 to Save DC (pick one), and add twice your ability modifier to damage rolls or Damage Reduction die to jutsu that add your modifier already.</p><p>Additionally, when a creature, other than yourself, takes damage from the Bleeding or Lacerated conditions, your seals draw in power from their blood loss, giving you the choice of recovering 7 hit points or gaining 7 temporary chakra points.</p>",
